  <div class="faq-section" id="faq">
    <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

    <details class="card">
      <summary>My Mermaid code isn't being detected</summary>
      <p>The first line of your code block must start with a supported diagram keyword (e.g. <code>graph TD</code>, <code>sequenceDiagram</code>, <code>erDiagram</code>). Comments (<code>%%</code>) on the first line will prevent detection. Move any comments below the keyword line.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="card">
      <summary>What permissions does the add-on need?</summary>
      <div>
        <p>The add-on uses two OAuth scopes:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="/changelog/#v1-1-0" title="Narrowed from `documents` in v1.1.0"><code>documents.currentonly</code></a> — access only the currently open document to read code snippets, insert diagrams, and import/export markdown</li>
          <li><code>script.container.ui</code> — display the editor and preview dialogs</li>
        </ul>
        <p>It cannot read, enumerate, or modify any other files in your Google Drive™.</p>
      </div>
    </details>

    <details class="card">
      <summary>Is my data sent to any server?</summary>
      <p>No. All diagram rendering happens 100% client-side in your browser using Mermaid.js. No document content, diagram code, or any other data is transmitted anywhere. See our <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a> for full details.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="card">
      <summary>Which diagram types are supported?</summary>
      <p>The add-on supports all major Mermaid diagram types including flowcharts, sequence diagrams, class diagrams, state diagrams, ER diagrams, Gantt charts, pie charts, git graphs, mindmaps, timelines, C4 diagrams, and more. See the <a href="/#diagrams">full list</a>.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="card">
      <summary>The add-on isn't showing in the Extensions menu</summary>
      <p>Try refreshing the page (Ctrl+R / Cmd+R). If it still doesn't appear, go to <strong>Extensions → Add-ons → Manage add-ons</strong> and verify that {{ site.title }} is installed and enabled.</p>
    </details>

